    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1969-09-05T11:15:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1969-09-05T11:15:00-05:00" n="114"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d114">
                <head>114. Notes of Telephone Conversation Between the President’s Assistant for
                    National Security Affairs (<persName corresp="#p_KHA1" type="from"
                        >Kissinger</persName>) and Secretary of State <persName corresp="#p_RWP1"
                        type="to">Rogers</persName>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d114fn1">Source: Library of Congress,
                        Manuscript Division, <persName corresp="#p_KHA1">Kissinger</persName>
                        Papers, Box 360, Telephone Conversations, Chronological File, 1–18 September
                        1969. No classification marking.</note>
                    <note n="2" type="summary" xml:id="d114fn2">
                        <persName corresp="#p_KHA1">Kissinger</persName> and <persName
                            corresp="#p_RWP1">Rogers</persName> discussed the 3 versus 12–mile
                        issue.</note>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                        when="1969-09-05T12:15:00-04:00">September 5, 1969, 12:15 p.m.</date>
                </dateline>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_RWP1">Rogers</persName> said he discussed the seabeds with
                    Mel. They are satisfied but they want to put something in the body that the
                    Soviets and we agree on 3-mile matter for other purposes or some such language.
                    We can’t put it in the body but could footnote it. <gloss target="#t_K1"
                        >K</gloss> said he talked to Mel and under these conditions we should go
                    ahead.</p>
                <p>[Omitted here is discussion unrelated to seabeds.]</p>
            </div>
        </body>
